        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p><addressee>Mr. I. Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Boston</placeName>, <date>Mai 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                    1848</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">An illness prevented me to write to you<lb/> any sooner. Nothing
                very important happened here.<lb/> The following officers were elected at the
                general meeting on <date>April 23rd</date>.</p>
            <list type="simple">
                <head/>
                <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. M. Ehrlich</persName>, Pres.</item>
                <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>H. P. Spitz</persName>, <sic>Vize</sic> Pres. &amp;
                    Treas.</item>
                <item rend="indent(1)">
                    <persName>C. W. Rosenfeld</persName>
                    <add>Trustee</add>
                </item>
                <item rend="indent(1)">
                    <persName>S. M. Peyser </persName>
                    <add>Trustee</add>
                </item>
                <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>M. Baiersdorfer</persName> Trustees</item>
                <item rend="indent(1)">
                    <persName>M. Disbecker</persName>
                    <add>Trustee</add>
                </item>
                <item rend="indent(1)">
                    <persName>H. Selling</persName>
                    <add>Trustee</add>
                </item>
                <item>and <persName role="author">B. Wurmser</persName> Secretary</item>
            </list>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Several members of our congre-<lb/>gation suggested the introduction
                of a 3 year c<del>i</del>ycle,<lb/> which of course means the abolition of the
                record<lb/> holiday and other reforms. This of course caused<lb/> hot debates, as
                could be expected particularly from the<lb/> Non German group. I believe, however,
                that this<lb/> plan will be adopted at the next G. M. on<lb/>
                <date>July 2nd</date>) my religion school impresses widely.<lb/> Owing to the kind
                    <del>support</del> collaboration of a lady, <persName>Mrs<lb/>
                    Lazarus</persName>, we have now nice<add>?</add> &amp; weeks a</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">2</p>
            <p>Sunday school and all of us tie by (story)<lb/> expectations to it for this lady
                really justifies my<add>?</add><lb/> expectations, for she has a wide knowledge,
                a<lb/> wonderful Jewish heart and a distinct preference<lb/> to teach. May the Lord
                bless her undertaking<lb/> and may her seeds open<add>?</add> in the heart of our children.<lb/>
                <add>Hevvah Ahavath Ahoth (the last word is wrong)</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our Ladies Hebrew Benevolent <del>An</del><lb/> Society had its G.
                M. yesterday (this society exist<lb/> now exactly one year and <del>has been</del> I
                was the one<lb/> who brought it to life). <persName>Mr. B. Fox</persName> became
                Pres.<lb/> and <persName>Mr. L. Lervingood</persName> became Vice Pres. And<lb/>
                Treas. And <persName role="author">B. Wurmser</persName> was the Secretary.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">How is your ____<add>Tefiloth</add><lb/> according
                    the____<add>Minhag (ritual)</add> of the German Jews<lb/> getting along? I am
                anxiously waiting.<lb/> Please forward 10 copies and of course<lb/> one free copy as
                soon as you get through<lb/> with it. You forgot <del>to Attach your</del> bill in
                your<lb/> parcel containing <sic>chatechisms</sic> for young children.<lb/> Please
                forward by return mail 3 more copies together<lb/> with your bill for all six.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If you have <add>alphabet <add>א"ב</add>
                </add><lb/> books, please send 6 copies along with them.<lb/> If you don't have them
                let me know where I can</p>
            <pb n="3R"/>
            <p>get them.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">No more for today.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">B. Wurmser</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>No. 8 Pleasant Street<lb/></placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <placeName>Court</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>PS. I expect the books by<lb/>
                <persName>Harnden's &amp; Co.</persName> Express<lb/> in a short time</p>
        </body>
